N:game-performance-profiler
D:Interpret Unity and Unreal performance evidence by turning screenshots, stat output, profiler captures, benchmark-route complaints, and Steam Deck/device review packets into one bottleneck-first profiling brief. Use when the next move is deciding CPU vs GPU vs memory vs streaming vs device risk, locking a reproducible route, and choosing the smallest useful next capture before optimization.
G:game-development unity unreal profiling performance frame-time hitch stat-unit stat-gpu unreal-insights steam-deck benchmark-route device-review quick-triage-packet

U[6]:
  Turn vague performance complaints into a quick evidence packet and next capture plan
  Classify likely bottlenecks across CPU, GPU, memory/GC, streaming, and device-specific risk
  Define reproducible routes, save slots, warm-up passes, and repeat counts for benchmark work
  Review Steam Deck or target-device packets without trusting editor numbers as final truth
  Choose whether to stay with stat/screenshots, move to engine profilers, or escalate to RenderDoc/PIX/Nsight
  Produce one profiling artifact: quick triage packet, profiling plan, benchmark route brief, or device review brief

S[8]{n,action,details}:
  1,Normalize,Record engine target environment symptom evidence route build/device context and quality variables first
  2,Mode,Choose one mode: quick-triage-packet bottleneck-classification benchmark-route-plan device-review or tool-escalation
  3,Classify,Pick one primary bottleneck bucket and optional secondary bucket before suggesting fixes
  4,Capture,Recommend the smallest next capture that can disambiguate the issue
  5,Route,Define save slot traversal path warm-up and repeat counts when reproducibility is missing
  6,Device,For Steam Deck/handheld review prioritize packaged-on-target evidence over editor impressions
  7,Escalate,Stay with quick packets or move to engine-native profilers before GPU-vendor tools unless render-side ambiguity remains
  8,Brief,Return a Game Performance Profiling Brief with Evidence packet Next capture Benchmark route/device review and one recommended next artifact

R[6]:
  Keep confidence low when the packet is screenshot-only or missing packaged/device context
  Do not jump to optimization advice before classifying CPU GPU memory streaming or platform/device risk
  Treat editor-vs-packaged as an explicit branch, not a footnote
  Prefer one repeatable route or save-based pass over vague location descriptions
  Use engine-native language first: Unity Profiler Frame Debugger Unreal Insights stat unit stat gpu
  Route broader demo prioritization to game-demo-feedback-triage generic app tuning to performance-optimization and build-system issues to game-ci-cd-pipeline or game-build-log-triage
